DC  Peptidoglycan Biosynthesis (Part 3)
DR  IUBMB; polysacc; PepGly3;
DC  Peptidoglycan biosynthesis I
DR  MetaCyc; PEPTIDOGLYCANSYN-PWY;
DC  Peptidoglycan biosynthesis II
DR  MetaCyc; PWY-5265;
CC  This property describes 10 well-conserved steps in the biosynthesis of
CC  UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-pentapeptide, a precursor of murein
CC  (peptidoglycan), from UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine. A few pathogenic
CC  genera, such as Borrelia and Rickettsia, appear to import
CC  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine from their host rather than synthesize it
CC  from fructose-6-phosphate (see GenProp0750).
--
